==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water ouzel
<hw>Wa"ter ou"zel</hw>
}</mhw>. <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species of small
insessorial birds of the genus <gen>Cinclus</gen> (or
<gen>Hydrobates</gen>), especially the European water ousel
(<spn>Cinclus aquaticus</spn>), and the American water ousel
(<spn>Cinclus Mexicanus</spn>). These birds live about the water, and
are in the habit of walking on the bottom of streams beneath the water
in search of food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water parsnip</ent>⟦br⟧
